# Reference Section Content

Grammar reference for understanding how Greek works: cases, pronouns, articles, verbs, adjectives, prepositions, and patterns.

## Route Structure

```
/reference                    Landing page with section cards
/reference/:tab               Grammar reference by topic
```

## Landing Page

<route path="/reference">
<purpose>Section hub - visual overview of all grammar reference topics</purpose>
<file>src/routes/reference/index.tsx</file>
<displays>
- Header: "Reference" with subtitle "Grammar patterns and paradigms"
- Section cards (7 items):
  - Cases: "The framework for understanding Greek grammar"
  - Pronouns: "Cases in action - the words you'll use most"
  - Articles: "Article paradigms and gender agreement"
  - Adjectives: "Agreement patterns that follow the noun"
  - Prepositions: "Connecting words and their case requirements"
  - Verbs: "Conjugation patterns and verb families"
  - Patterns: "Greek-specific constructions like μου αρέσει"
- Each card links to /reference/{section}
</displays>
<note>
Cards use colour-coded borders matching tab colours (ocean, olive, honey, terracotta).
</note>
</route>

## Tabs

```
cases        → Case system foundation (nominative, accusative, genitive)
pronouns     → Pronoun paradigms and decision guides
articles     → Article paradigms and gender agreement
adjectives   → Adjective agreement patterns
prepositions → Preposition + case combinations
verbs        → Verb conjugation patterns
patterns     → Greek-specific constructions (NEW - moved from phrases)
```

